oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of the USS Finland
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This image shows the USS Finland docked at Newport News, Virginia. The 114th Field Artillery sailed back from Europe on the Finland. The Finland was originally an ocean liner for the Red Star Line built in 1902. During World War I, she served initially as a transport for the Army but transferred to the Navy in April 1918. She returned over 32,000 troops to the US at wars end. The photograph belonged to Musician Kenneth Redford, HQ Co., 114th FA, 30th Div. Redford was from Franklin, Tennessee.
